## Proposed Changes

> Prioridad: la versión imprimible es el deliverable principal; la vista en pantalla debe optimizarse para print fidelity (preview a escala) y no al revés.

#### Routing

#### [MODIFY] [index.astro](file:///Users/cenco/Github/galiprandi/me/src/pages/index.astro)
- Change import from [./tl/index.astro](file:///Users/cenco/Github/galiprandi/me/src/pages/tl/index.astro) to [./em/index.astro](file:///Users/cenco/Github/galiprandi/me/src/pages/em/index.astro)
- Render `<EMPage />` instead of `<TLPage />`

#### [ADD] Redirect `/tl` → `/em`
- Add a redirect rule so legacy links to `/tl` land on the new CV (`/em`). If Astro supports static redirects, configure it there; otherwise add a lightweight middleware/route handler.

#### Layout (New 2-Page CV Layout)

Instead of modifying [Layout.astro](file:///Users/cenco/Github/galiprandi/me/src/layouts/Layout.astro) (which is shared with `/tl`, `/ext`, `/porfolio`), the `/em` page will get a **self-contained layout** to avoid breaking other routes.

#### [MODIFY] [index.astro](file:///Users/cenco/Github/galiprandi/me/src/pages/em/index.astro)
Complete rewrite. **This becomes the master 2-page CV page** with its own inline layout.

**Key design decisions:**
- Each page is a `<div class="cv-page">` with `height: 297mm` (A4) for precise print control.
- Dark sidebar (`#1e293b` slate-800) with white text.
- Header repeats on both pages (compact version).
- Footer tagline repeats on both pages.
- Axioma section in a subtle highlighted box (`background: #f8fafc`, border-left accent).
- Experience items simplified: **bold title + light date** pattern, bullet points only.
- Screen preview should mirror print proportions: center two stacked pages on wide screens with subtle shadow; avoid styles that diverge between screen and print except for `@media print` overrides.

### Styling

#### [MODIFY] [global.css](file:///Users/cenco/Github/galiprandi/me/src/styles/global.css)
- Add CSS custom properties for the dark sidebar palette.
- Add `.cv-page` class with `height: 297mm`, `box-sizing: border-box`.
- Add print-specific `@page` rules ensuring clean 2-page split.
- Definir márgenes orgánicos para impresión: `@page { size: A4; margin: 12mm 14mm; }` y en `.cv-page` usar paddings fluidos (p. ej. `padding: 18mm 16mm 16mm`) para mantener proporciones sin recortes.
- Controlar cortes de página: `.cv-page { break-after: page; }`, y `break-inside: avoid` en bloques clave (experiencia, sidebar sections, axioma) para evitar splits incómodos.
- Tipografía y densidad: fuente sans consistente con el sitio, `line-height: 1.35–1.4`, tamaños calibrados (ej. body 10.5–11pt, headings 12–16pt) y listas con `margin-block: 0.25em 0.4em` para encajar en 2 páginas.
- Ajustes de bullets: limitar longitud de ítems y espaciar con `gap` corto; usar `max-width` en columna principal si hace falta para evitar desbordes en print.
- Add `.cv-sidebar` and `.axioma-box` styles.

## Verification Plan
1. **Browser Validation**: Run `pnpm dev` and verify rendering at `http://localhost:4321/me/`.
2. **Print Validation**: Trigger `Cmd+P` on the page and verify exactly 2 A4 pages are generated via browser print preview.
3. **Redirection Check**: Abrir `/tl` y confirmar que redirige a `/em`.
4. **SEO/OG Check**: Validar en `view-source:` que `<title>`, `<meta name="description">` y OG/Twitter apunten a la versión `/em` y describan el CV.

## SEO/Metadata
- Actualizar `<title>` y `<meta name="description">` de `/em` para posicionarlo como CV canónico.
- Actualizar meta OG/Twitter (title, description) y `og:url` a `/em`.
- Incluir `rel="canonical"` apuntando a `/em`.
